  "texts": [
    "One issue raised by the use of a multiplexed code is how the fly brain produces the correct behaviour at the correct time.",
    "For example, LPLC2 neurons synapse onto the giant fibre neuron to drive an escape take-off 25, but our 1-to-1 network predicts that this same cell type encodes female size and contributes to the forward velocity of the male during courtship (Fig. 5a); recent work has also found LPLC2 contributes to evasive flight turns 38.",
    "Future experiments are needed to understand how the same LC cell type can contribute to different behaviours in different contexts.",
    "Our modelling approach comes with limitations.",
    "For example, if silencing an LC type does not lead to a noticeable change in behaviour, the 1-to-1 network cannot infer the tuning of that LC type."
  ],
